page.content: The woods in the Parks are of course for conservation and recreational use. The roads and hills in the area are no obstacles for traffic. Going from the south of our area towards the north we descend to the River Thames and before we reach the river we either pass under or cross over the London to Woolwich/Gravesend line, British Rail, Southern Region, so a great part of the area is therefore flat. The only part of our area covered by water is the 2km of the River Thames. There are small sections of derelict land in the area but these will soon be built on. Large buildings which have been pulled down are now used as temporary Car or Coach Parks or for small housing estates. Most of the new buildings in the area are either houses, maisonnettes or very low blocks (4 floors) or flats.
